By default, Express does not set `Access-Control-Allow-Origin`. Depending on deployment, this may be too permissive or cause breakage.

**Fix:** Explicitly configure [`cors`](https://www.npmjs.com/package/cors):
```js
const cors = require('cors');
app.use(cors({ origin: process.env.ALLOWED_ORIGIN || 'https://yourdomain.com' }));
```

#### 6. Hardcoded Port
Port `3000` is hardcoded. This is an operational and security concern (predictability, privilege escalation).

**Fix:**
