app.listen(PORT, () => {
  console.log(`Server running on port ${PORT}`);
});
```

### 6. No Request Body Parsing or Size Limiting
If POST/PUT routes are added later without a body-size limit, the app is vulnerable to large payload attacks.

**Fix:** Add body parsers with size limits upfront:
```js
app.use(express.json({ limit: '10kb' }));
app.use(express.urlencoded({ extended: true, limit: '10kb' }));
```

### 7. CORS Not Configured
By default, Express allows all origins or none explicitly. You should explicitly declare your CORS policy:
```js
